<!-- ABOUT -->
<section id="about">
  <div class="section-header reveal">
    <span class="section-label">01</span>
    <h2 class="section-title">About</h2>
    <span class="section-line"></span>
  </div>

  <div class="about-grid">
    <div class="about-text reveal">
      <p>
        I am a Professor and Bioinformatics Scientist with <strong class="highlight">15+ years of experience</strong> applying Next-Generation Sequencing (NGS) across medicine, biotechnology, pharmaceuticals, agriculture, and biodiversity. I bring a profound understanding of the field that facilitates innovation and enables seamless integration of bioinformatics techniques into production environments.
      </p>
      <p>
        I founded and led bioinformatics capabilities operating at production scale, integrating NGS wet-lab workflows, reproducible computational pipelines, and HPC/cloud infrastructure. I am trusted to plan, prioritize, and execute multiple concurrent bioinformatics initiatives — often 8+ in parallel — translating scientific and client needs into robust analytical systems and actionable insight.
      </p>
      <p>
        My domain expertise spans <strong class="highlight">precision medicine and oncology</strong>, rare disease genomics, microbiome therapeutics, agricultural biotechnology, and single-cell biology, with extensive wet lab and in silico expertise combined with leadership experience across both academic and private sectors.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="about-aside reveal">
      <div class="aside-block">
        <div class="aside-block-title">Domain Expertise</div>
        <span class="domain-tag">🧬 Precision Medicine</span>
        <span class="domain-tag">🔬 Single-Cell Biology</span>
        <span class="domain-tag">🧪 NGS Workflows</span>
        <span class="domain-tag">🦠 Metagenomics</span>
        <span class="domain-tag">🧫 Transcriptomics</span>
        <span class="domain-tag">💊 Drug Development</span>
        <span class="domain-tag">🌿 Agricultural Genomics</span>
        <span class="domain-tag">🤖 ML / Computational</span>
        <span class="domain-tag">🏥 Clinical Bioinformatics</span>
        <span class="domain-tag">📊 Multi-Omics</span>
      </div>
      <div class="aside-block">
        <div class="aside-block-title">Languages</div>
        <div style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:8px">
          <div style="display:flex;justify-content:space-between;align-items:center">
            <span style="font-size:13px;color:var(--text2)">🇦🇷 Spanish</span>
            <span style="font-family:var(--mono);font-size:11px;color:var(--accent)">Native</span>
          </div>
          <div style="display:flex;justify-content:space-between;align-items:center">
            <span style="font-size:13px;color:var(--text2)">🇬🇧 English</span>
            <span style="font-family:var(--mono);font-size:11px;color:var(--accent)">Advanced</span>
          </div>
          <div style="display:flex;justify-content:space-between;align-items:center">
            <span style="font-size:13px;color:var(--text2)">🇧🇷 Portuguese</span>
            <span style="font-family:var(--mono);font-size:11px;color:var(--accent)">Proficient</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- EXPERIENCE -->
<section id="experience">
  <div class="section-header reveal">
    <span class="section-label">02</span>
    <h2 class="section-title">Experience</h2>
    <span class="section-line"></span>
  </div>

  <div class="experience-list">

    <div class="exp-item reveal">
      <div class="exp-meta">
        <div class="exp-period">Aug 2021 – Present</div>
        <div class="exp-org">Stamm Vegh<br/>Corporation</div>
      </div>
      <div class="exp-content">
        <div class="exp-role">Bioinformatics Manager &<br/>Head of Bioinformatics Division</div>
        <ul class="exp-bullets">
          <li>Founded and scaled a multidisciplinary bioinformatics function — defining organizational structure, technical direction, and delivery models across NGS, multi-omics analytics, and bioinformatics software development.</li>
          <li>Planned, prioritized, and delivered a high-complexity portfolio of 8+ concurrent bioinformatics initiatives spanning precision medicine, cancer genetics, single-cell transcriptomics, metagenomics, and agricultural genomics.</li>
          <li>Owned end-to-end execution including pipeline architecture, algorithm and platform development, HPC/cloud infrastructure, and client-ready outcomes ensuring reproducibility and regulatory alignment.</li>
          <li>Designed and implemented the company's NGS laboratory including long-read technologies (PacBio & Oxford Nanopore), personally validating assays and translating wet-lab protocols into production-grade pipelines.</li>
          <li>Acted as scientific and technical authority at the interface of bioinformatics, software engineering, wet-lab operations, and external partners.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="exp-item reveal">
      <div class="exp-meta">
        <div class="exp-period">Jul 2015 – Present</div>
        <div class="exp-org">Independent<br/>Consultant</div>
      </div>
      <div class="exp-content">
        <div class="exp-role">Scientific R&D Advisor — Bioinformatics & NGS</div>
        <ul class="exp-bullets">
          <li>Founded and operated an independent consultancy supporting healthcare, biotech, and academic organizations in genomics, NGS, and data analytics.</li>
          <li>Designed and implemented scalable data pipelines for clinical, translational, and biotechnology applications, translating scientific questions into actionable analytical solutions.</li>
          <li>Applied AI and machine learning approaches to biological datasets, providing expert domain guidance for model training, evaluation, and interpretation in biomedical contexts.</li>
          <li>Developed ontology-driven biological annotation and classification frameworks supporting AI model development and structured data curation.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="exp-item reveal">
      <div class="exp-meta">
        <div class="exp-period">Jul 2020 – Present</div>
        <div class="exp-org">UADE University</div>
      </div>
      <div class="exp-content">
        <div class="exp-role">University Professor — Bioinformatics & Data Analytics</div>
        <ul class="exp-bullets">
          <li>Designed and led postgraduate training programs integrating NGS, AI-driven analysis, and computational health systems.</li>
          <li>Organized international postgraduate courses; mentored professionals in applied bioinformatics and data visualization for healthcare and life sciences.</li>
          <li>Bridge academic training with industry practice, emphasizing reproducibility, scalable pipelines, and real-world decision-making.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="exp-item reveal">
      <div class="exp-meta">
        <div class="exp-period">2019 – 2021</div>
        <div class="exp-org">CONICET – UBA<br/>Argentina</div>
      </div>
      <div class="exp-content">
        <div class="exp-role">Postdoctoral Researcher — Bioinformatics & Genomics</div>
        <ul class="exp-bullets">
          <li>Led genomics and transcriptomics projects in infectious diseases, integrating multi-omics data to uncover disease mechanisms.</li>
          <li>Published and presented findings through peer-reviewed journals and international conferences.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="exp-item reveal">
      <div class="exp-meta">
        <div class="exp-period">2017 – 2019</div>
        <div class="exp-org">University of<br/>Edinburgh, UK</div>
      </div>
      <div class="exp-content">
        <div class="exp-role">Postdoctoral Researcher — Bioinformatics & Genomics</div>
        <ul class="exp-bullets">
          <li>Directed genomic diversity and infectious disease research using next-generation sequencing and computational pipelines.</li>
          <li>Collaborated with international teams on large-scale genomics initiatives with global research partners.</li>
          <li>Coordinated data analysis, visualization, and manuscript development across interdisciplinary groups.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="exp-item reveal">
      <div class="exp-meta">
        <div class="exp-period">2009 – 2013</div>
        <div class="exp-org">INTA & Barenbrug-<br/>Palaversich Co.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="exp-content">
        <div class="exp-role">R&D Scientist — Agricultural Biotechnology</div>
        <ul class="exp-bullets">
          <li>Conducted research on pest control strategies, agricultural biotechnology, and soybean inoculant improvement at national R&D institutions.</li>
          <li>Utilized genetic engineering to modify organisms as a method for crop yield improvement across integrated project teams.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div>
</section>

